ious reports had issues because we added a file without sufficient coverage. It's possible JUnit's method order isn’t direct enough. I have this idea that using Class.forName could help, but it gets tricky with test class initialization and static references. The test methods don’t seem to run before the order is set, which raises some concerns.\n\n**Examining class loading and coverage**\n\nI’m thinking about how to force an active system class helper call through a public API, but I’m unsure if coverage agents ignore synthetic class calls because classes might be initialized before instrumentation. I wonder if calling methods via reflection could still work with Class.forName. If that class is already loaded, the GraalVM agent may not generate reflect-config since it wasn’t accessed reflectively. Class.forName returns the class but no members, which makes me question whether the native agent records queried classes properly.\n\n**Analyzing call site coverage**\n\nI’m looking at how the call site can still be \"uncovered,\" even though the execution instrumentation might see it as covered. It seems like this involves using a Java agent without needing specific config. I should consider the outcome of Class.forName for reflective operations that the agent tracks. The static init passes the class to LogFactory.getLog instead of doing anything reflective. It makes me wonder if the dynamic access coverage system is custom because invoking MethodHandles access might not work since the class name is a String parameter from the test.\n\n**Analyzing code and checks**\n\nI'm considering a check with AssertJ to handle throwing callables and whether Checkstyle might flag something, especially a line over 100 characters. If Checkstyle fails, how would the user react? Then I thought about adding a direct call to Class.forName. I wonder if it’s necessary to run certain checks or just inspect the current file for line length and order. There’s a lot to think through in this process!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05d9d5d369d9db6d016a04b0f1aef08195b4ee748012a96047\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBLEGnmkjNWiXUscowJHmDh3V2ugZnye7WVuyiCMDDWtr6TZvSAvqhX-ZY4oiQ1PHeZ0LHAs3-xFcasAlkmT_fPwRGHzV5x_7sG6UtR8P9l8BnbQqdJgQBSRv7tsTnTRPCYOIpJpIAZCqxtJD7n4vDlcFRJBc-Tce2Xfs3C3sC1JKgrPfi6U4ReAcPxi-jV5nUf76XG1ierC9MKaYeZwykZJrB5F1gMEyc7hdKDaDgaWWGEo8a57xKKZsvvwMdFDlWc6wOyhPjXZ0XpVrpU5Htydp5iCDJ1kIQjURWmSdvCQ_9d6I19XwGXFRRhxDXY-PvWyNshEnk-aKKhkxORhhQ319-Ni1aVYxERiaia39KqKoPhy1ivK-gcfIW-hY26Wq3t5rIlTgRuPtTFhVC8pGzgLHXqmgnaTw9JHASVEQEntmYkO3ejcoistkcwvUHcKUYK4a63n3UPoB-vCyUYxYdvzO9b7bCLZZQZ5Do-uLtrTow44rJ7BxUka_4Y4ZQlNMFNCnM6uQRXFsrplWoJEtREKw9vAYiwYhNtdPSV-EAexUN68xRE8QABnJhnBcAIfOxiE0qqopXQLWdeZkP5pMvqEYF3bLEU6pNyE2vMINDmZbjctSXaXR78zBTtJ-1HstpWLDmJSjDKf3ixTuhaFLU_Fwon-sN60pX1PMgbVxjB_4bf17NRHpOgyWCfz6ZuqTa7uGjYj0MaVUnG2w9qA_kCUGRpYOHYK5qNLlYcjCYF6zre3Lncx4SbR8plhv6R5NHOsN9YlYegeHJM_6_2cszBD9B-Mv6ucCpi0WCVMBTKRo5nCo4juQLhb4jQuInULVrkY60L9_mYwno8YxVKuKXqkR3vdJ73QSoSCUlEdeexaV4wkLcjJVoi-NLq0oxa4CHlx5JFhRw07WxTKA0O3G0k-u1OC4NgTosS9D8LbRVoN-xJ0jSW_RsM8W1WVRNM82fBa78GbagtM8KJmIbSsQF0j_Ny_vUUXReLh9EU9tKnyQE5r_HD4bhdQmVqtd1wXqTWakXRDZ9qJdO8tvP51IA24G0KpWIPj7u4xzcfSbUjczDcNbbBF4CMms-vIyEUC_bT5mWrZ2L-cIv-5Efl60FL4VFaNk_SksEXW7oK_QDxugjiIckrvONaPJSqJm96zSO5jIKgean3nNQeltEDCR_-nYtGRaFf-k5dtbB5NV86fUdJ69fatMYwMZMolqxsyOjm4uMBwBMFMrF4LP1xwjyeDhhuMz36AUe1Z0ioc-tjUOmGeRfI5xludiwZ-zd9pmEJszN6IBxybnihgJSQ-a9T4yA4nVX-PDMX8MuFQEB0e2UYqZ8hPvpOnfJyY0_NlzdFrzfiuhNGx6vKIiPKdDQnLHBRhAGqpm7Un0ICMWIVi4oFv8lInDOhk08NBtP4c6Zgu-m_RNPmWJinQuJHCkQYKGvIO1PpeIJxY6NpoygkCDffJ2-ZGb3wQusBmT0LAFvAN-FANTRNS5idGIi9SspjArJ3FkQcafzKZuYcX-4Plu3tEBZdqqHbJnW87UaKqRmz9PnfLe6mMEKbrt_v3p95H0OXZOIBKMd4ZXQHLYsJskoKBic8Vy-_4Rukog9ZRsBhBonHa4dxoxBpuCQUiQV_6Dvv7D3nT7liJ9xOQ6JO-HHl5Wxcgh9FT2QXtrn5oVp0kLO36LuJZlNslNHLZQ17Zrg1xHFHszAdbbJ8Rh2lwiJINpZPzWyQCfl0avywJAu48n-m3cADfOmhYVSGC3-g_K1LDwUgv_vWvpaihKmwS9ZeTPEYfY2nSXBPegKVOGgjJCOQ49yIv-xb9KVgEHrdDIGfLzM8frIuKIy9zTOfs82tfI-LyoAS2faXH